                     <interp inst="t17920912-51-person522" type="given" value="SEBASTIAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920912-51-person522" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I lost a child's hat, on the 22d of August last; the prisoner asked me leave to go out repeatedly, at last I gave him leave to go out; and I finished this hat in the morning; I suspected him, and took him in Soho Square; he had nothing in his pocket but a few yards of galloon; I saw the constable take the hat from behind him; he was committed.</p>

               <p>- KENNEDY sworn.</p>
               <p>I found the hat inside his breeches.</p>
               <p>(The hat deposed to.)</p>
               <p>There is a private mark on the side of it with chalk.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>On the Monday before this, my master and me had a great many words, about my bed and bedding not being put to rights, and he made me work on Sundays.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17920912-51-verdict277" type="verdictDescription">
